answers.answer: Hi there!While there are several causes that could cause a false positive test, false negative test could result from inadequate dosages. Though protein in urine could cause a negative test; urinary protein/ renal disease would need to be demonstrated in such a case.Hope this information is useful.Take care!

question: I have had type1 diabetes for 35 years.  I am prescribed fentanyl patch for failed back surgery syndrome.  The doctor gives a urine and lab test to make sure I am taking the meds because the DEA? or whoever it is is cracking down on him. the problem is it doesn't show on my test.  he says it could be because of protein in urine.  does anyone know if this could be true?  Other meds I take do show up.  my brother says maybe i am getting fake meds because some companies are getting cheaper meds from overseas and they aren't what they are supposed to be.
